CHALLENGES OF GROUP PROJECTS

Challenges

 

  1. Tremendous diversity of skills
  2. Ensuring good group chemistry
  3. Limited time (…but considerable resources)
  4. Different goals?
  5. Balancing your individual contribution with the collective effort

RESEARCH SPEED DATING

Research Speed-dating

  1. We crowdsource a list of research interests in a google doc (5 min)
  2. Each person writes a “1” next to their research interests (5 min)
  3. We identify maximally similar clusters
  4. Maximally similar clusters come up with a group project (30 min)
  5. We identify maximally different clusters
  6. Maximally different clusters come up with a group project (30 min)
  7. We hear from Gary King
  8. Lunch
  9. Everyone adds their favorite group project idea to a google spreadsheet (10 minutes)
  10. Everyone puts there name next to the group project they want to join (10 minutes- group level discussion encouraged!)

Maximally similar

 

#read in interests from google sheet
library(gsheet)
our_interests<-gsheet2tbl('docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1bm-1tD9dPAr73gAUP-2nN24IKQPFteJwAToRyOROefA')
#create distance matrix
distance_matrix <- dist(our_interests, method = "euclidean") 
fit <- hclust(distance_matrix, method="ward") 
# display dendogram
plot(fit, labels=our_interests$Name) 
groups <- cutree(fit, k=4) # cut tree into 5 clusters
# draw dendogram with red borders around the 5 clusters 
rect.hclust(fit, k=4, border="red")

Simulate Random Groups

 

final<-as.data.frame(NULL)
data$names<-NULL
library(dplyr)
library(vegan)
for (i in 1:1000){
test<-sample_n(our_interests, 4)
names<-paste0(test$Name, collapse=", ")
diversity_score<-diversity(test[,c(2:ncol(test))])
data<-cbind(names, mean(diversity_score))
final<-rbind(final, data)
print(i)
}
names(final)<-c("group","diversity_score")

Identify maximally diverse groups

 

final$diversity_score<-as.character(final$diversity_score)
final$diversity_score<-as.numeric(final$diversity_score)
final<-final[order(final$diversity_score, decreasing=TRUE),]
